            . I live at <placeName id="t18100221-79-crimeloc470">No. 9, Susannah-row, Curtain-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18100221-79-crimeloc470" type="placeName" value="No. 9, Susannah-row, Curtain-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18100221-79-crimeloc470" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18100221-79-off466 t18100221-79-crimeloc470"></join>. I am a carpenter, in the employ of Mr. Hall. I was informed, that there was a load of wood came from Copthall-court. Mr. Butler asked me, to lend him six-pence to make up the money for the load of wood. The prisoner had six shillings and eight-pence for the load of wood, and a pint of beer.</p>
               <p>MR. BUTLER. I heard the agreement between Mr. Hall and the prisoner. I borrowed six-pence to pay him the six shillings and eight-pence.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in liquor. I was not quite sure that I had taken the money, and therefore I booked the work.</p>
               <p>GUILTY.</p>
